FORMER Zimbabwean first Lady, Grace Mugabe’s first husband, Wing commander Stanley Goreraza has died on Sunday morning. Goreraza battled with cancer for a long time. A notice about his death was shared at a flat he owned in Harare. “Good morning. I hope I find you all well! It is with a heavy heart that we announce the passing of our dear friend, Stanley Goreraza. He passed away this morning after a long battle with cancer and stroke. May his dear soul rest in peace,” the notice read. Goreraza was an officer in the Air Force of Zimbabwe. He served as a defence attaché in China at the Zimbabwean Embassy until his untimely death. He was formerly married to Grace Mugabe for 13 years and they divorced in 1996 after it was revealed to the public that Grace had two children by the former Zimbabwe president Robert Mugabe. Grace and Stanley have one child together, Russell Goreraza. Stanley was studying in China in the year 2000 and was appointed Zimbabwe’s defence attaché to China in January 2001. In 2006, he was honoured for his long service in the Air Force of Zimbabwe and received a bar to his long and exemplary service medal.